# UI Components Architecture

Portal uses a comprehensive component system built on shadcn/ui with Radix UI primitives and TailwindCSS.

## Component Organization

### Core UI Components (`/components/ui`)
Base components following shadcn/ui patterns:
- `button.tsx`: Button variations with cva styling variants
- `form.tsx`: React Hook Form integration with validation
- `dialog.tsx`, `sheet.tsx`, `drawer.tsx`: Modal and overlay components  
- `dropdown-menu.tsx`, `popover.tsx`: Contextual menus and overlays
- `table.tsx`: Data table with sorting and pagination
- `sidebar.tsx`: Navigation sidebar with collapsible sections
- `input.tsx`, `textarea.tsx`, `select.tsx`: Form input components
- `calendar.tsx`: Calendar picker for date selection
- `card.tsx`, `badge.tsx`, `avatar.tsx`: Content display components

### Shared Components (`/components/shared`)
Cross-application reusable components:
- `combobox.tsx`: Search and select with autocomplete
- `date-time-picker.tsx`, `date-range-picker.tsx`: Advanced date/time selection
- `tiptap-editor.tsx`: Rich text editor with multiple modes
- `activity-section.tsx`: Activity timeline display
- `event-dialog.tsx`, `event-popover.tsx`: Calendar event management
- `table/`: Advanced table components with pagination and sorting
- `content-with-copy.tsx`: Content display with copy functionality

### Domain-Specific Components
**Dashboard (`/components/dashboard`)**:
- `header.tsx`: Main dashboard header with breadcrumbs and search
- `sidebar.tsx`: Navigation sidebar with user context
- Subdirectories organized by feature (account, contact, resource, workspace)

**Landing (`/components/landing`)**:
- `header.tsx`, `footer.tsx`: Marketing page layout components

**Root (`/components/root`)**:
- `layout.tsx`: Root application layout
- `provider.tsx`: Global providers (theme, analytics, progress)

## Component Patterns

### shadcn/ui Pattern
```tsx
import { cva, type VariantProps } from 'class-variance-authority';
import { cn } from '@/lib/utils';

const buttonVariants = cva(
  "inline-flex items-center justify-center rounded-md text-sm font-medium",
  {
    variants: {
      variant: {
        default: "bg-primary text-primary-foreground hover:bg-primary/90",
        destructive: "bg-destructive text-destructive-foreground",
        outline: "border border-input bg-background hover:bg-accent",
        // ... more variants
      },
      size: {
        default: "h-10 px-4 py-2",
        sm: "h-9 rounded-md px-3",
        lg: "h-11 rounded-md px-8",
        icon: "h-10 w-10",
      },
    },
    defaultVariants: {
      variant: "default",
      size: "default",
    },
  }
);

export interface ButtonProps
  extends React.ButtonHTMLAttributes<HTMLButtonElement>,
    VariantProps<typeof buttonVariants> {
  asChild?: boolean;
}

const Button = React.forwardRef<HTMLButtonElement, ButtonProps>(
  ({ className, variant, size, asChild = false, ...props }, ref) => {
    const Comp = asChild ? Slot : "button";
    return (
      <Comp
        className={cn(buttonVariants({ variant, size, className }))}
        ref={ref}
        {...props}
      />
    );
  }
);
```

### Form Integration Pattern
```tsx
import { useForm } from 'react-hook-form';
import { zodResolver } from '@hookform/resolvers/zod';
import { Form, FormControl, FormField, FormItem, FormLabel } from '@/components/ui/form';

const formSchema = z.object({
  name: z.string().min(1, 'Name is required'),
});

export function MyForm() {
  const form = useForm<z.infer<typeof formSchema>>({
    resolver: zodResolver(formSchema),
  });

  return (
    <Form {...form}>
      <FormField
        control={form.control}
        name="name"
        render={({ field }) => (
          <FormItem>
            <FormLabel>Name</FormLabel>
            <FormControl>
              <Input {...field} />
            </FormControl>
          </FormItem>
        )}
      />
    </Form>
  );
}
```

### Advanced Component Examples

#### Combobox with Search
```tsx
export function Combobox({ items, value, onChange, allowCustom = false }) {
  const [open, setOpen] = useState(false);
  const [query, setQuery] = useState('');
  
  return (
    <Popover open={open} onOpenChange={setOpen}>
      <PopoverTrigger asChild>
        <Button variant="outline" role="combobox">
          {value || "Select item..."}
          <ChevronsUpDown className="ml-2 h-4 w-4 shrink-0 opacity-50" />
        </Button>
      </PopoverTrigger>
      <PopoverContent className="w-[200px] p-0">
        <Command>
          <CommandInput
            placeholder="Search..."
            value={query}
            onValueChange={setQuery}
          />
          <CommandEmpty>
            {allowCustom ? (
              <Button onClick={() => onChange(query)}>
                Create "{query}"
              </Button>
            ) : (
              "No results found."
            )}
          </CommandEmpty>
          <CommandGroup>
            {items.map((item) => (
              <CommandItem key={item} onSelect={() => onChange(item)}>
                <Check className={cn("mr-2 h-4 w-4", value === item ? "opacity-100" : "opacity-0")} />
                {item}
              </CommandItem>
            ))}
          </CommandGroup>
        </Command>
      </PopoverContent>
    </Popover>
  );
}
```

#### Rich Text Editor
```tsx
export function TipTapEditor({ content, onChange, editable = true }) {
  const editor = useEditor({
    extensions: [StarterKit, Link, Image],
    content,
    onUpdate: ({ editor }) => {
      onChange(editor.getHTML());
    },
    editable,
  });

  return (
    <div className="border rounded-lg">
      <Toolbar editor={editor} />
      <EditorContent
        editor={editor}
        className="prose max-w-none p-4"
      />
    </div>
  );
}
```

## Styling Patterns

### TailwindCSS Integration
- Use `cn()` utility for class merging
- Implement consistent spacing and typography scales
- Follow design system color palette
- Use responsive design patterns

### Dark Mode Support
```tsx
// Automatic dark mode support through CSS variables
.dark {
  --background: 0 0% 3.9%;
  --foreground: 0 0% 98%;
  --primary: 0 0% 98%;
  --primary-foreground: 0 0% 9%;
}
```

### Component Variants
- Use `class-variance-authority` for consistent variant patterns
- Implement size, color, and behavior variants
- Provide sensible default variants
- Support composition through `asChild` pattern

## Accessibility

### ARIA Patterns
- Proper ARIA labels and descriptions
- Keyboard navigation support
- Focus management for modals and dropdowns
- Screen reader compatibility

### Form Accessibility
- Associate labels with form controls
- Provide validation feedback
- Support keyboard navigation
- Clear error messaging

## Performance Optimizations

### Code Splitting
- Lazy load heavy components (TipTap editor)
- Use dynamic imports for conditional components
- Optimize bundle size with tree shaking

### Rendering Optimizations
- Use React.memo for expensive components
- Implement proper dependency arrays
- Avoid unnecessary re-renders
- Use callback optimization patterns

## Theme System

### CSS Variables
- Consistent color system across light/dark modes
- Scalable spacing and typography
- Component-specific CSS custom properties

### Provider Setup
```tsx
export function ThemeProvider({ children }) {
  return (
    <NextThemesProvider
      attribute="class"
      defaultTheme="system"
      enableSystem
      disableTransitionOnChange
    >
      {children}
    </NextThemesProvider>
  );
}
```

## Component Testing

### Testing Patterns
- Unit tests for component logic
- Integration tests for form workflows  
- Accessibility testing with jest-axe
